    <text>       
        <body>
            <div type="poem">
                <head><hi rend="caps">Sabbath Morning</hi></head>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="1">
                    <head>I</head>
                    <l><hi rend="caps">See</hi> where the sun on that hill doth arise</l>
                    <l>And look where <persName ref="#Phoebus">Phoebus</persName> snatches up his
                        reins</l>
                    <l>See where his radiance paints the morning skies</l>
                    <l>And where unwillingly the darkness wanes.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="2">
                    <head>II</head>
                    <l>The dewdrops glitter to the rising sun</l>
                    <l>With diamonds decking all the trees so fair</l>
                    <l>Frail in their beauty melting one by one</l>
                    <l>And in a vapour thickening all the air.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="3">
                    <head>III</head>
                    <l>Lo where invited by the genial heat</l>
                    <l>Forth come the bees rejoicing in the sun</l>
                    <l>From each fair flow&#x02019;r they suck their honey sweet</l>
                    <l>Forming a gentle music with their hum.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="4">
                    <head>IV</head>
                    <l>Above in robe of blue adorned so fair</l>
                    <l>Speckled with small white clouds is that soft sky</l>
                    <l>Which gently float upon the balmy air</l>
                    <l>Hiding the skylark as it warbles high.</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="5">
                    <head>V</head>
                    <l>And now the birds awake and sweetly sing</l>
                    <l>Hailing the sunny morn and azure sky</l>
                    <l>Now from their nests upon the air they spring</l>
                    <l>And brave the clouds as happily they fly</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="quatrain" rhyme="abab" n="6">
                    <head>VI</head>
                    <l>Now born on waving air the church bell rings</l>
                    <l>Pleasing the ear as tolls it softly slow</l>
                    <l>Sound following sound full heavily it swings</l>
                    <l>And in sweet cadence rolls in music low</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
